issue.title: bad substitution error
issue.body:
When including the line: 

    [[ -z ${fpath[(r)$HOME/.zsh/completion]} ]] && fpath=(~/.zsh/completion $fpath)

I my vim syntax pluging complains: 

    .zshrc: bad substituion 

And the file does not seem to be loading, am I doing something wrong? 
ps The the directory $HOME/.zsh/completion exists with the _perlbrew completion file in it.

comment.body: I thought I found something, your checking with -z, but checking if the dir exists should be with -d right? This doesn't solve the issue, but i thought i mention it.

issue.title: Use RACK_ENV for heroku?
issue.body:
Hi,

I wonder why RAILS_ENV is used instead of RACK_ENV when pushing to heroku, as the latter is the standard config key used throughout Cedar. Figaro's current implementation requires the user to add a redundant config key to the stack (`heroku config:add RAILS_ENV={same-as-RACK_ENV}`) before using the rake task.

comment.body: Figaro isn't intended for pure Rack apps. The new way in which Figaro looks for your remote `Rails.env` (as of v0.6.2) should properly read `RAILS_ENV` from Heroku.

issue.title: Travis doesn't run all tests
issue.body:
Travis runs selftest.py which is a quick&small testing script; the "real" test suite is in Tests folder.

Maybe re-enabe py32 and add this to .travis.yml: `python Tests/run.py --installed`?

comment.body: Ah! Well that explains it :-) Thanks
